name: @extendscript/aes.patch.array.lastindexof
description: The lastIndexOf() method returns the last index at which a given element can be found in the array, or -1 if it is not present. The array is searched backwards, starting at fromIndex.

scripts.env: if [ ! -f ./build-node-venv.sh ]; then curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ES-CPP/bashnips/master/build-node-venv.sh > ./build-node-venv.sh; fi; chmod +x ./build-node-venv.sh && ./build-node-venv.sh && # npm install && npm update
